First Department,

May, 1961

(May 2, 1961) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. David Moseley, Appellant.

Judgment of conviction unanimously affirmed. The errors assigned by the appellant must be disregarded in view of the competent evidence which clearly establishes his guilt of the crime charged ( Code Grim. Pro., § 542). Concur — Botein, P. J., Breitel, McNally, Steuer and Bergan, JJ.
